parameters.description: The caller is required to set Avi Version Header to the expected version of configuration. If unset, the version will be defaulted to 16.4.3. The response from the controller will provide and accept data according to the specified version. The controller will reject POST and PUT requests where the data is not compatible with the specified version.

usable_network_uuids.description: Usable networks for Virtual IP. If VirtualService does not specify a network and auto_allocate_ip is set, then the first available network from this list will be chosen for IP allocation. Field introduced in 17.1.3.

resource_group.description: Azure resource group dedicated for Avi Controller. Avi Controller will create all its resources in this resource group. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

use_enhanced_ha.description: Use Azure's enhanced HA features. This needs a public IP to be associated with the VIP. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

usable_domains.description: Usable domains to pick from Azure DNS. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

usable_network_uuids.description: Usable networks for Virtual IP. If VirtualService does not specify a network and auto_allocate_ip is set, then the first available network from this list will be chosen for IP allocation. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

egress_service_subnets.description: Used for allocating egress service source IPs. Field introduced in 17.2.8.

use_standard_alb.description: Use Standard SKU Azure Load Balancer. By default Basic SKU Load Balancer is used. Field introduced in 17.2.7.

azure_serviceprincipal.description: Service principal based credentials for azure. Only one of azure_userpass or azure_serviceprincipal is allowed. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

azure_userpass.description: User name password based credentials for azure. Only one of azure_userpass or azure_serviceprincipal is allowed. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

subscription_id.description: Subscription Id for the Azure subscription. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

virtual_network_ids.description: Virtual networks where Virtual IPs will belong. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

ip_addr.description: Placeholder for description of property ip_addr of obj type IpAddrPrefix field type str  type object

use_iam_roles.description: Use IAM roles instead of access and secret key.

publish_vip_to_public_zone.description: If enabled and the virtual service is not floating ip capable, vip will be published to both private and public zones. This flag is applicable only for AWS DNS profile. Field introduced in 17.2.10.

usable_domains.description: Usable domains to pick from Amazon Route 53. Field introduced in 17.1.1.

ttl.description: Default TTL for all records. Allowed values are 1-172800. Field introduced in 17.1.3.

zones.description: Network configuration for Virtual IP per AZ. Field introduced in 17.1.3.

iam_assume_role.description: IAM assume role for cross-account access. Field introduced in 17.1.1.

usable_network_uuids.description: Usable networks for Virtual IP. If VirtualService does not specify a network and auto_allocate_ip is set, then the first available network from this list will be chosen for IP allocation. Field introduced in 17.1.1.

tenant_id.description: Tenant ID for the subscription. Required for application id based authentication only. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

application_id.description: Application Id created for Avi Controller. Required for application id based authentication only. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

authentication_token.description: Authentication token created for the Avi Controller application. Required for application id based authentication only. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

record_ttl.description: TTL value for DNS records. Allowed values are 1-604800.

num_dns_ip.description: Specifies the number of A records returned by Avi DNS Service. Allowed values are 0-20. Special values are 0- 'Return all IP addresses'.

domain_name.description: Service domain string used for FQDN.

pass_through.description: Third-party Authoritative domain requests are delegated toDNS VirtualService's pool of nameservers.

azure_profile.description: Provider details if type is Microsoft Azure. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

openstack_profile.description: Provider details if type is OpenStack.

_last_modified.description: UNIX time since epoch in microseconds. Units(MICROSECONDS).

name.description: Name for the IPAM/DNS Provider profile.

gcp_profile.description: Provider details if type is Google Cloud.

infoblox_profile.description: Provider details if type is Infoblox.

tenant_ref.description: It is a reference to an object of type Tenant.

allocate_ip_in_vrf.description: If this flag is set, only allocate IP from networks in the Virtual Service VRF. Applicable for Avi Vantage IPAM only. Field introduced in 17.2.4.

custom_profile.description: Provider details if type is Custom. Field introduced in 17.1.1.

aws_profile.description: Provider details if type is AWS.

internal_profile.description: Provider details if type is Avi.

type.description: Provider Type for the IPAM/DNS Provider profile. Enum options - IPAMDNS_TYPE_INFOBLOX, IPAMDNS_TYPE_AWS, IPAMDNS_TYPE_OPENSTACK, IPAMDNS_TYPE_GCP, IPAMDNS_TYPE_INFOBLOX_DNS, IPAMDNS_TYPE_CUSTOM, IPAMDNS_TYPE_CUSTOM_DNS, IPAMDNS_TYPE_AZURE, IPAMDNS_TYPE_INTERNAL, IPAMDNS_TYPE_INTERNAL_DNS, IPAMDNS_TYPE_AWS_DNS, IPAMDNS_TYPE_AZURE_DNS.

uuid.description: UUID of the IPAM/DNS Provider profile.

username.description: The username Avi Vantage will use when authenticating to Keystone.

vip_network_name.description: Network to be used for VIP allocation.

password.description: The password Avi Vantage will use when authenticating to Keystone.

username.description: Username for API access for Infoblox appliance.

usable_domains.description: Usable domains to pick from Infoblox.

usable_subnets.description: Usable subnets to pick from Infoblox.

password.description: Password for API access for Infoblox appliance.

is_dynamic.description: Placeholder for description of property is_dynamic of obj type CustomParams field type str  type boolean

is_sensitive.description: Placeholder for description of property is_sensitive of obj type CustomParams field type str  type boolean

username.description: Username for Azure subscription. Required only for username password based authentication. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

tenant_name.description: Tenant or the active directory associated with the subscription. Required for user name password authentication. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

password.description: Password for Azure subscription. Required only if username is provided. Field introduced in 17.2.1.

match_se_group_subnet.description: Match SE group subnets for VIP placement. Default is to not match SE group subnets. Field introduced in 17.1.1.

use_gcp_network.description: Use Google Cloud Platform Network for VIP allocation. By default Avi Vantage Network is used for VIP allocation. Field introduced in 18.1.2.

project_name.description: Google Cloud Platform Project Name. This is required if Google Cloud Platform Network is used for VIP allocation. This field is optional. By default it will use the value of the field network_project_name. Field introduced in 18.1.2.

region_name.description: Google Cloud Platform Region Name. This is required if Google Cloud Platform Network is used for VIP allocation. Field introduced in 18.1.2.

network_project_name.description: Google Cloud Platform Network Project Name. This is the host project in which Google Cloud Platform Network resides. Field introduced in 18.1.2.

usable_network_refs.description: Usable networks for Virtual IP. If VirtualService does not specify a network and auto_allocate_ip is set, then the first available network from this list will be chosen for IP allocation. It is a reference to an object of type Network.

network_name.description: Google Cloud Platform Network Name. VIP will be allocated from this Network. This is required if Google Cloud Platform Network is used for VIP allocation. Field introduced in 18.1.2.

usable_network_refs.description: Usable networks for Virtual IP. If VirtualService does not specify a network and auto_allocate_ip is set, then the first available network from this list will be chosen for IP allocation. It is a reference to an object of type Network.

dns_virtualservice_ref.description: Avi VirtualService to be used for serving DNS records. It is a reference to an object of type VirtualService.

ttl.description: Default TTL for all records, overridden by TTL value for each service domain configured in DnsServiceDomain. Allowed values are 1-604800.

custom_ipam_dns_profile_ref.description: It is a reference to an object of type CustomIpamDnsProfile. Field introduced in 17.1.1.

dynamic_params.description: Custom parameters that will passed to the IPAM/DNS provider including but not limited to provider credentials and API version. Field introduced in 17.1.1.
